From David Nye Subject Re seizures infantile spasms reply to MD After many metabolic tests body structure tests and infection virus tests the doctors still do not know quite what type of siezures he is having although they do have alot of evidence that it is now pointing to infantile spasms This is where we stand right I know now these particular types of disorders are still not really well understood by the medical Infantile spasms have been well understood for quite some time You are seeing a pediatric neurologist aren't you If not I strongly recommend There is a new anticonvulsant about to be released called felbamate which may be particularly helpful for infantile As for learning more about seizures ask your doctor or his nurse about a local support David Nye Midelfort Clinic Eau Claire WI This is patently absurd but whoever wishes to become a philosopher must learn not to be frightened by Bertrand Russell